<DOC><DOCNO> AP880524-0127 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-24-88 1247EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--China-Storm     05-24 0137</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--China-Storm,0140</SECOND><HEAD>Chinese Storm Wrecks 1,000 Homes</HEAD><DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A storm that killed 78 people in one province ofsoutheastern China has wrecked 1,000 homes elsewhere, it wasreported Tuesday.   The official Xinhua News Agency said 42 bridges were alsodamaged and 1,200 miles of highway flooded in Jiangxi province. Nocasualties were reported.   The rains, which began Friday, dumped up to a foot of water onsome parts of neighboring Fujian. Officials have reported 78 peopledead in the northern part of the province, more than 200 injured,and more than 3,100 forced to flee their homes.   Unusual weather has plagued much of China this month. Hailstormskilled at least 24 people and injured more than 250 in coastal andcentral China, and a tornado in Guangdong province in southeasternChina killed five people.</TEXT></DOC>